1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,626
Delivery plans change.
Driver authority should not.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,260
PITT keeps the route visible while traffic,
weather, work zones, and fuel conditions move.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:21,000
When a delivery day changes, drivers must reconcile time windows,
fuel reserve, detours, and exception paperwork.

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,500
Navigation finds a route.

5
00:00:24,500 --> 00:00:29,640
PITT explains whether changing it is worthwhile,
and records what happened.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:39,000
At each predicted presence time, PITT checks historical traffic,
a rain band moving west to east, and a seeded road-work register.

7
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:46,153
Their delays move through the schedule.
Every prototype signal is explicitly non-live.

8
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:54,727
Fuel combines pump price with detour cost.
The lowest price is not automatically the best decision.

9
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Outcome one. The price rises.
PITT displays the impact and waits.

10
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:07,936
The driver chooses the revised fuel stop,
restoring the simulated reserve.

11
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Outcome two. The driver passes the hike.
Later, the price drops.

12
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:24,959
Pump and detour cost now make the stop worthwhile,
so the driver refuels.

13
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:36,500
Outcome three. The tank was filled that morning.
Cheaper fuel appears, but its small saving cannot recover another detour.

14
00:01:36,500 --> 00:01:43,422
Cheap fuel is not always economical fuel.

15
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Outcome four. The driver passes twice.
Fuel reaches zero.

16
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:02,421
PITT blocks unsafe continuation and offers to close the route early.
The driver confirms; remaining stops stay recorded as undelivered.

17
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Codex and GPT-5.6 helped shape the rules, find the missing branch,
and test all four outcomes in the browser.

18
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:27,080
Codex also provided moral support when the demo fought back.
Every consequential action remains behind driver review.

19
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:35,292
PITT produces a reviewable report and local machine handoff.
It contacts no carrier and controls no vehicle without an approved next step.

20
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:44,555
And yes. PITT is aware of magic roundabouts.
Swindon still gets human review... and possibly a wizard.
